isions, cover with clean, dry gauze. Your steri-strips will fall off on their own. Please remove any remaining strips 7-10 days after surgery. Please call the doctor if you have increased pain, swelling, redness, or drainage from the incision sites.", "category": "Category 9: Advice and precaution", "start_offset": "6432", "end_offset": "6763", "annotation_id": "KG_072"}, {"decision": "Please follow up with Dr. [**Last Name (STitle) **] [**Name (STitle) 23**] building [**Location (un) 470**] on Friday [**6-10**] @ 1:30.", "category": "Category 1: Contact related", "start_offset": "6789", "end_offset": "6925", "annotation_id": "KG_073"}, {"decision": "Please call and make an appointment to have her infectious disease physician [**Name Initial (PRE) 788**]. Dr. [**First Name4 (NamePattern1) 7568**] [**Last Name (NamePattern1) 79**].", "category": "Category 1: Contact related", "start_offset": "6927", "end_offset": "7110", "annotation_id": "KG_074"}]}